text: Carneades grandis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Thomson in 1860. It is known from Belize, Honduras, and Mexico.BioLib.cz - Carneades grandis. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Colobotheini Category:Beetles described in 1860
title: Carneades grandis
